12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 58 O.S. 2021, Section 246, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 246. A. Upon the filing of the petition and combined
16 notice, the court shall dispense with the regular estate proceedings
17 prescribed by law and the court shall order notice to creditors and
18 issue an order granting final hearing upon the petition for
19 admission of the will, if any, to probate, the petition for summary
20 administration, the final accounting, and the petition for
21 determination of heirship, distribution and discharge. However,
22 nothing in this section shall affect the lien upon any property for
23 any estate or transfer tax which may be due upon the estate of the
24 decedent.
